, \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A dazzling laser show that lit up the Eiffel Tower did its best to pierce the leaden skies over Paris but two hours of unrelenting rain ensured a sodden start for an Olympic opening ceremony like no other.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.872564501558578e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, a sodden-looking Tom Daley and Helen Glover held the Union flag aloft in front of the 37 other hardy GB athletes willing to expose themselves to the dismal conditions.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.871088652995318e-29, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 2033, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9997755095670219, \"rank\": 0.00011427520489854843, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, wwo masked figures featured in the opening ceremony, first as a mysterious torchbearer ran across rooftops before a caped rider galloped down the Seine on a metal horse to deliver the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8707870164388351e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rider, a non-commissioned officer in theGendarmerie Nationaleclad in silver armour, concluded her ride at the Trocadero, giving the Olympic flag a majestic entrance before it was hoisted - although the wrong way round.\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, a figure wearing a black cloak, white hood and with their face covered by a dark fencing mask was heavily featured in the three--and-a-half-hour ceremony.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Produced by director Thomas Jolly, the show included appearances from Lady Gaga, Zinedine Zidane and, for some reason, The Minions, before finishing with Dion's return.\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2721, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9980466030123769, \"rank\": 0.0011136693101689217, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}, {\"begin\": 2770, \"end\": 2779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 56-year-old singer said in late 2022 that she had been diagnosed with a rare neurological disorder called stiff-person syndrome that causes muscle spasms.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 3028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The syndrome causes muscle rigidity and increased sensitivity to sound, touch and emotional stimuli that can trigger spasms.\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The condition led the multiple Grammy winner to cancel all of her tour dates for 2023 and 2024.\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadian singer, who started her career singing in French, has not performed live since March 2020, when she appeared in New Jersey.\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3256, \"end\": 3264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9997166301953975, \"rank\": 0.0002833158772093993, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3307, \"end\": 3313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999261018177387, \"rank\": 5.9582036219558406e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3377, \"end\": 3387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.9999187794540494, \"rank\": 6.782187002840502e-05, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dion made a comeback to the live stage on Friday singing Edith Piaf's classic \\\"L'Hymne A l'Amour\\\" to close the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3571, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.257996247985431e-17, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"